+6.7.8.1 (29.04.26)
+
+- Application ID handling became saner. Default data directory name changes from Yukigram to io.github.yukigram. To use new paths from an older installation, rename Yukigram folder to io.github.yukigram in ~/.local/share/ (unisolated package, e.g. static binary, AUR or manual build) or in ~/.var/app/io.github.yukigram/data/ (nixpak, flatpak)
+- Window class changes from Yukigram to io.github.yukigram
+- Remove second "Message" button in peer info box if the first one is already shown
+- Yukigram settings are moved to separate settings page and categorized: tg://settings/yukigram
+- Yukigram settings can now be searched for (try pressing Ctrl+F and typing yukigram in settings)
+- Some experimental settings are also present on Yukigram settings page and are searchable
+- Allow using monochrome (symbolic) tray icon from icon theme: tg://settings/yukigram/icon-theme-symbolic. Telegram Desktop assumes GNOME symbolic recoloring (adapting to theme color) mechanism. KDE uses a different algorithm and therefore requires using icons from icon themes (e.g. Breeze Icons) instead of bundled ones. As Yukigram exposes its icons with a different application id (io.github.yukigram instead of org.telegram.desktop), this override does not happen and bundled symbolics are used. This option allows to use telegram icons from icon theme by using official icon names instead of patched ones. Telegram Desktop and Yukigram can still be installed alongside one another, install phase is not affected, only tray icon rendering code is
+- Allow hiding channels requiring Premium in "Send As" menu: tg://settings/yukigram/hide-send-as-premium
+- Allow hiding "Send As" button completely: tg://settings/yukigram/hide-send-as
+- Peer type icons in history are now hidden by default: tg://settings/yukigram/history-peer-type-icons
+- Allow hiding reply background emoji: tg://settings/yukigram/hide-reply-background-emoji
+- Channel statistics are accessible from kebab menu near Recent Actions button
+- Incorrectly names itself "Yukigram (Debug)"
+
